reg:regulation.reg:title: Mountain Caribou Partnership General Remission Regulation (No. 2)

bcl:definition.bcl:text: affected coal lease means a lease under the Coal Act that is identified by number in Table 1 of this regulation;
affected coal licence means a licence under the Coal Act that is identified by number in Table 2 of this regulation;
affected mineral claim means a mineral claim under the Mineral Tenure Act that is identified by number in Table 3 of this regulation;
affected year means any of the 2021, 2022 and 2023 calendar years;
deferral period means the period beginning on June 21, 2021 and ending on June 20, 2023.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text: Authorization is given for the remission of the eligible portion, determined in accordance with subsection (2), of the following amounts:

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text: an amount paid under section 13 (3) (a) [term and extension of licence] of the Coal Act in relation to an affected coal licence and an affected year;
an amount paid under section 20 [payment of rent for lease] of the Coal Act in relation to an affected coal lease and an affected year;
an amount paid under section 29 (a) [continuation of claims] of the Mineral Tenure Act in relation to an affected mineral claim and an affected year.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text: For the purposes of subsection (1), the eligible portion of an amount that is paid in relation to an affected year is the product of

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text: the quotient of the number of days in the affected year that are within the deferral period and 365.

reg:content.reg:provisionsnote: [Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Financial Administration Act, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 138, s. 19.]
